==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rattlebox
<hw>Rat"tle*box`</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧t"t'l*b⟦ocr⟧ks`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A toy that makes a rattling sound; a rattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An American herb
(<spn>Crotalaria sagittalis</spn>), the seeds of which, when ripe,
rattle in the inflated pod.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any species of
<spn>Crotalaria</spn>, a genus of yellow-flowered herbs, with inflated,
many-seeded pods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rattle-brained</ent>⟦br⟧
